  "prompt": "What are some songs that make you cry?",
  "response": "Music has a unique ability to evoke deep emotions, and many people have songs that can make them cry due to their melodies, lyrics, or personal associations. Here are a few songs that are often cited for their emotional impact:\n\n1. **\"Tears in Heaven\" by Eric Clapton** - Written about the loss of his son, this song touches on themes of grief and longing.\n\n2. **\"Hallelujah\" by Leonard Cohen (and popularized by Jeff Buckley)** - A hauntingly beautiful song that blends themes of love, loss, and redemption.\n\n3. **\"The Night We Met\" by Lord Huron** - This song captures the pain of yearning and lost love.\n\n4. **\"Fix You\" by Coldplay** - Known for its comforting yet emotional vibe, it offers a message of support during tough times.\n\n5. **\"Goodbye My Lover\" by James Blunt** - A poignant reflection on the end of a meaningful relationship.\n\n6. **\"Cats in the Cradle\" by Harry Chapin** - A narrative about missed opportunities and the passage of time between a father and son.\n\n7. **\"The A Team\" by Ed Sheeran** - Touches on themes of addiction and vulnerability.\n\n8. **\"Someone Like You\" by Adele** - A powerful ballad about coming to terms with a past relationship.\n\n9. **\"My Heart Will Go On\" by Celine Dion** - Famous from the film \"Titanic,\" it conveys enduring love and loss.\n\n10. **\"Hurt\" by Nine Inch Nails (and covered by Johnny Cash)** - An introspective song dealing with regret and pain.\n\nThese songs often resonate with listeners due to their lyrical depth and the soulful delivery of the artists.",
